<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="cat-page-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cat-page-faq-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked questions</span>
      <h2>What people ask us most about injectables.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="cat-page-faq-list">
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item open">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Botox or hyaluronic acid? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Botox relaxes muscles (forehead, frown lines, crow's feet). Hyaluronic acid restores lost volume (folds, lips, contour). During the diagnosis we identify what you actually need — often it's both, in different areas.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Does it hurt? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Minimally. The needles are extremely fine. In sensitive areas we apply a numbing cream beforehand. Most patients describe the sensation as a brief pinch.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">When will I see results? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Botox: progressive effect between day 3 and day 14 (full effect at 2 weeks). Hyaluronic acid: visible within hours, full effect at 2-4 weeks. Threads: immediate lifting plus collagen stimulation at 3 months. PRP: results at 4-6 weeks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">How long do they last? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Botox: 4-6 months depending on area. Hyaluronic acid: 6-12 months depending on product. Barbed threads: 12-18 months. PRP: 6-12 months with maintenance sessions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Pregnancy or breastfeeding? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Injectables are contraindicated during pregnancy and breastfeeding. We wait until you finish breastfeeding before starting any plan.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FINAL CTA -->
